VCGI reprojected the imagery from its original coordinates system (UTM Z18) to VT State Plane Meters (NAD83). For this dataset, the natural color orthoimages were produced at 0.3-meter pixel resolution (approximately 1-foot). There is no image overlap between adjacent files. The naming convention is based on the U.S. National Grid (USNG), taking the coordinates of the SW corner of the orthoimage.</dct:description>
